<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Return true if this shuffle mask is a transpose mask.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Transpose vector masks transpose a 2xn matrix. They read corresponding</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// even- or odd-numbered vector elements from two n-dimensional source</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// vectors and write each result into consecutive elements of an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// n-dimensional destination vector. Two shuffles are necessary to complete</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the transpose, one for the even elements and another for the odd elements.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This description closely follows how the TRN1 and TRN2 AArch64</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// instructions operate.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// For example, a simple 2x2 matrix can be transposed with:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   ; Original matrix</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   m0 = &lt; a, b &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   m1 = &lt; c, d &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   ; Transposed matrix</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   t0 = &lt; a, c &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1, &lt; 0, 2 &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   t1 = &lt; b, d &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1, &lt; 1, 3 &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// For matrices having greater than n columns, the resulting nx2 transposed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// matrix is stored in two result vectors such that one vector contains</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// interleaved elements from all the even-numbered rows and the other vector</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// contains interleaved elements from all the odd-numbered rows. For example,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// a 2x4 matrix can be transposed with:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   ; Original matrix</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   m0 = &lt; a, b, c, d &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   m1 = &lt; e, f, g, h &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   ; Transposed matrix</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   t0 = &lt; a, e, c, g &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1 &lt; 0, 4, 2, 6 &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   t1 = &lt; b, f, d, h &gt; = shufflevector m0, m1 &lt; 1, 5, 3, 7 &gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/shufflevectorinst/#a28026e5094b94a512f9116384eed7c93"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/shufflevectorinst/#a28026e5094b94a512f9116384eed7c93">isTransposeMask</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;int&gt;</a> Mask, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumSrcElts) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
